{"key":"processedPost-8954814","value":{"id":8954814,"first":8954791,"last":8955069,"when":1221851830,"utime":"09/19/08 10:17 PM","content":"Yes, treat uncased substrates as cakes, which by definition are uncased substrates.<br />You can easily dunk a bulk substrate.&nbsp; I prefer to do it under the faucet with very gently running water so that the tray overflows and the excess runs down the drain.&nbsp; Weigh the substrate with whatever you have to set on top to hold it down. A mason jar or two full of water works well.&nbsp; The moving water seems to help re-hydration and it also washes away contaminant spores.<br />RR","title":"Re: Uncased substrate should be treated exactly like a cake. Right!?"}}